Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.77,0:01:34.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out, one of the twelve disciples...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.29,0:01:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister Angelene!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.87,0:01:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister Angelene!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.94,0:01:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.71,0:01:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't show me something as pathetic as that!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.84,0:01:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, use this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.10,0:01:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.12,0:02:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An escape pod.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.60,0:02:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a better alternative than staying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.44,0:02:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister Lucia, your hand's shaking...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.76,0:02:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.28,0:02:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, I'm not going to die here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.82,0:02:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll all go back together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.66,0:02:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You... as well as everyone else fighting here...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.01,0:02:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone will be together...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.44,0:02:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I won't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.96,0:02:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, please... fight your hardest to protect everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.08,0:02:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say something, Lucia.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.59,0:02:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help if possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.63,0:02:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it means destroying as many\Nof these stupid illusions as I have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.64,0:03:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So say something that will make her think it was worth being here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.47,0:03:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something that will make her believe it was worth gritting her teeth!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.33,0:03:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.73,0:03:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll protect everyone, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.15,0:03:14.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, please, you have your own fight right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.01,0:03:30.02,TOARUnextepisode,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\fs65.5\t(0,2200,\fscx90\fscy90)\c&H821213&\fsp-2\move(562,645,573,615,0,2250)}To{\fsp-7}a{\fsp0}ru Ma{\fsp-7}j{\fsp-7}u{\fsp-7}t{\fsp-4}s{\fsp-2}u no {\fsp-4}I{\fsp-2}n{\fsp-4}d{\fsp-4}e{\fsp-2}x
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.56,0:03:34.48,TOARUepisodetitle,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(670,849)\bord2.5\fs45\fsp-3\pos(974,576)}Appo{\fsp-6}inte{\fsp-2}d Time\Nof{\fsp-10} {\fsp-2}the Rosary
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.90,0:03:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are they still at it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.76,0:03:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.75,0:03:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think we'd have to go through\Nso much trouble just to sink one city.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.92,0:03:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That face...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.02,0:03:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Absolutely wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.80,0:03:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That expression that says you still believe in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.65,0:03:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what would I believe in?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.91,0:03:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to break your hopes now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.34,0:04:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've no need for such emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.46,0:04:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.54,0:04:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get that girl at all costs!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.10,0:04:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Index, Orsola!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.72,0:04:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody seems to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.86,0:04:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This ship is most likely monitoring the entire fleet using magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.99,0:04:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'd explain why the Sisters haven't followed us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.57,0:04:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.85,0:04:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll unlock it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.08,0:04:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starting to get a little tired of thinking things through!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.63,0:04:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.02,0:04:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A block structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.75,0:04:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike the escort ships, this ship has\Nmagic embedded throughout its structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.24,0:04:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those knights...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.10,0:04:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.08,0:04:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.02,0:04:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.86,0:05:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys go on ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.49,0:05:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Touma!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.44,0:05:13.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister Angelene, are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.44,0:05:17.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.84,0:05:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they weren't my comrades...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.02,0:05:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.34,0:05:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.05,0:05:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop picking on the injured girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.76,0:05:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap, another one!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.92,0:05:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.48,0:05:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another one?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.65,0:05:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.02,0:06:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It connected!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.09,0:06:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Orsola?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.09,0:06:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Touma, is it true that, to activate The Queen of The Adriatic Sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.70,0:06:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they need to cast another spell called\N"Appointed Time of the Rosary"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.53,0:06:11.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.25,0:06:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My 103,000 grimoires say nothing about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.16,0:06:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what kind of a spell is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.89,0:06:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's a codename only known by\Nmembers of the Roman Catholic Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.93,0:06:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That right hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.81,0:06:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.35,0:06:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not one bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.50,0:06:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not only does it cancel out the blessing of the Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.88,0:06:54.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you swing it around like it's some sort of weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.78,0:06:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you had ever heard God's teachings,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.89,0:07:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then you would do anything to receive his\Nblessings, even if you had to rip your arm off!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.29,0:07:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose the language of humans would\Nmake no sense to a pagan monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.14,0:07:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I, Biagio Buzoni, will put an end to this enemy of the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.85,0:07:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're Biagio?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.98,0:07:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means you know where Agnese is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.15,0:07:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knowing and telling are two very different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.45,0:07:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cross is the way of repentance!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.35,0:07:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cross can eliminate enemies, as well\Nas provide a safe zone anywhere near it.{外敵を排し内部に安全地帯を作るための役割を十字架は持つ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.67,0:07:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.01,0:07:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Additionally, the cross also holds the\Npower to correct a man of his pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.86,0:08:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again... just like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.60,0:08:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.96,0:08:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.10,0:08:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Must you break everything around you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.81,0:08:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might affect the purity of the spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.20,0:08:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.51,0:08:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Appointed Time of the Rosary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.64,0:08:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't pretend you know nothing of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.57,0:08:29.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter. This will be over if I\Ncrush you and get Agnese out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.94,0:08:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really going against the will of the Lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.44,0:08:35.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such evil words.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.70,0:08:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My crosses will reject that evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.14,0:08:43.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.46,0:08:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think you have the right to do whatever you want with Venice?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.57,0:08:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is not my intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.55,0:08:52.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.49,0:08:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, it's a hundred times more\Ninteresting than what you're thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.19,0:09:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what the oldest execution tool in Christianity is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.38,0:09:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Execution tool, I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.23,0:09:12.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simon bears the cross of the Son of God!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.35,0:09:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.05,0:09:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cross is the way of repentance!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.58,0:09:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.84,0:09:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a defensive spell on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.51,0:09:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C.A.H.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.31,0:09:43.56,TOARUSigns3,,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad2.5\c&HFEFFFF&\fs53\pos(641,593)\b1}Shift focus onto me
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.14,0:09:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go get Agnese!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.60,0:09:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll keep these guys busy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.70,0:09:50.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Index-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.29,0:10:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Orsola Aquinas?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.54,0:10:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.21,0:10:09.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.79,0:10:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you not want to escape The Queen's Fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.09,0:10:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you know what you're getting yourself into?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.95,0:10:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once we understood the situation at\Nhand, not one person wished to flee.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.04,0:10:28.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They did not wish to leave you as a sacrifice and run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.06,0:10:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.61,0:10:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You remember what I did for The Book of the Law, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.34,0:10:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you just save me after everything we've been through?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.39,0:10:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, myself, do not know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.48,0:10:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Lucia and Angelene-san swore to save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.48,0:10:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even in the midst of a desperate situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.00,0:10:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and even when they had an infinite number of blades pointing at them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.27,0:10:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They wanted to save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.92,0:11:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that not enough of a reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.68,0:11:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use, Sister Agnese.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.57,0:11:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you die here, the operation will go on as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.61,0:11:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But finding another compatible person is such a tedious task.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.02,0:11:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I {\i1}really{\i0} hate things that are tedious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.46,0:11:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.07,0:11:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said I hate tedious things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.79,0:11:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I crushed him in the quickest manner possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.01,0:11:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather not have to do it again here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.75,0:11:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't have you hurt for our plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.44,0:11:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The anti-Venice large-scale spell...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.41,0:11:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you activating it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.53,0:11:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not trying to use the anti-government attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.38,0:11:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's something beyond that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.89,0:12:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Queen of the Adriatic Sea is a spell\Nmade only to be used against Venice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.14,0:12:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how compelling it seems, if we can't\Nundo the lock-on limitation, then it has no point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.12,0:12:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.25,0:12:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you've realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.93,0:12:19.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're undoing the lock-on limitation\Nof The Queen of the Adriatic Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.83,0:12:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what The Appointed Time of the Rosary is for.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.54,0:12:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that you plan to destroy all cities that are in your way?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.66,0:12:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Queen of the Adriatic Sea destroys\Neverything connected to the city!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.90,0:12:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think would happen if we aimed\Nit at the city where the enemy kingdom lies?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.30,0:12:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Academy City?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.68,0:12:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All kinds of science are connected to Academy City's technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.62,0:13:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we destroy it, we can destroy everything that has to\Ndo with the other half of the world in a single night!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.33,0:13:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that will make everyone happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.66,0:13:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.02,0:13:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that there are evildoers on the magic side.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.38,0:13:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they can continue whatever they were doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.58,0:13:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, all those impurities will be eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.68,0:13:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.87,0:13:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what the Roman Catholic Church wishes for.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.71,0:13:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cross is the way of repentance!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.62,0:13:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just stop, Sister Orsola.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.74,0:13:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The burden of the cross chastises the proud!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.09,0:13:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, we're ahead of schedule, but\Nhow about we start this, Sister Agnese?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.20,0:13:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rejoice!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.67,0:13:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You will go down in history as the one who eradicated\Nthe largest number of enemies to Christianity in history!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.23,0:13:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those "enemies" you speak of...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.06,0:14:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They include Agnese, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.10,0:14:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fear because you now belong to the Church of England.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.52,0:14:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really can't act on anything but suspicion, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.56,0:14:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand what it means to act on hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.87,0:14:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or, though you do understand, you cannot bring yourself to believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.22,0:14:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please move.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.29,0:14:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way you can stop Biagio.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.09,0:14:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't stand up to him you can make it out of here alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.62,0:14:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.82,0:14:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the end, Sister Orsola.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.67,0:14:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad, Sister Agnese.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.39,0:14:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both your dreams are about to be crushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.42,0:14:47.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.71,0:14:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All things correspond with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.21,0:14:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of the five elements, one of the fifth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.95,0:14:53.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The symbol of peace and order.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.91,0:14:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Expand the Bishop's Staff!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.20,0:14:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister Agnese!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.30,0:15:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked you what the meaning of this was!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.15,0:15:03.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.74,0:15:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm probably wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.72,0:15:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm wrong to want to continue taking care of\NSister Lucia, Sister Angelene, and the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.34,0:15:17.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I think of all the Sisters who are out\Nthere, fighting because of your stupid order...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.16,0:15:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes my blood boil.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.02,0:15:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't speak as if you're so high and mighty, you sinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.86,0:15:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simon bears the cross of the Son of God!{oh. simon. k.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.90,0:15:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If my memory serves, the Son of God did not\Nhave the strength to carry the cross himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.80,0:15:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simon carried it up the hill for the execution instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.42,0:15:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.98,0:15:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You realized it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.76,0:16:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The true form of this attack is in\Nmaking the enemy bear a heavy weight!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.99,0:16:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You focus the weight of all the personnel and\Nequipment here onto one point and turn it into weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.87,0:16:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something like that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.90,0:16:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That weak hand of yours can't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.70,0:16:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to need a stronger hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.45,0:16:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.84,0:16:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about this right hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.46,0:16:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.08,0:16:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You pagan monkey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.36,0:16:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, at least make sure I'm dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.45,0:16:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My right hand isn't as easy to beat as you think!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.68,0:16:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.85,0:16:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like that'd work on me twice!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.12,0:16:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agnese.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.52,0:17:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.03,0:17:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.08,0:17:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you hadn't protected Orsola, things would have gone a lot worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.00,0:17:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.98,0:17:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how do we go about destroying\NThe Queen of the Adriatic Sea entirely?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.26,0:17:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this room can't be changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.89,0:17:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we completely destroy its functions, they can never reconstruct—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.21,0:17:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agnese!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.19,0:17:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agnese! What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.42,0:17:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Appointed Time of the Rosary...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.12,0:17:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.84,0:17:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's activated it and has done something to Agnese!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.41,0:17:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't use it without proper adjustments.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.21,0:17:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have all the power I need right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.09,0:18:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Roman Catholic Church feared that the\Nweapon might be stolen and turned against us,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.32,0:18:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so all those restrictions and limits were put into place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.93,0:18:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if it ever did fall into the hands of the enemy,\Nwhat do you think their last resort would be?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.86,0:18:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A self-destruct?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.43,0:18:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a large-scale magical tool supported\Nalchemically by this entire fleet of sinners.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.11,0:18:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go thinking that simply destroying the walls or floors can stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.08,0:18:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the sheer amount of magic in here, the\Nexplosion will be at least 10 kilometers wide...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.78,0:18:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There will be casualties on land, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.47,0:18:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agnese!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.58,0:18:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Orsola, take Agnese and get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.55,0:18:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get the Amakusa people to leave, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.78,0:19:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.53,0:19:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.44,0:19:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I promise I'll meet up with you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.42,0:19:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just go, Orsola!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.42,0:19:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.13,0:19:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.10,0:19:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.82,0:19:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Carve your name into Roman Catholic history," my ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.79,0:19:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told him it was too early for a plan like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.29,0:19:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done for.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.71,0:19:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're going to take down everything with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.08,0:19:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end all you want to do is console yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.13,0:19:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody wouldn't feel that this situation is dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.56,0:19:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the ultimate will of the Roman Catholic Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.76,0:19:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone would agree with my decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.94,0:19:52.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the last flower that will bloom in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.78,0:19:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will gladly destroy the coast of the Adriatic Sea for that goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.92,0:19:57.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Biagio!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.99,0:19:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That look!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.96,0:20:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That look of persistence is exactly what threatens us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.79,0:20:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that is why I will be sure to destroy you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.19,0:20:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That will be my final legacy to the Roman Catholic Church!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.81,0:20:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Biagio!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.85,0:20:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cross is the way of repentance!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.33,0:20:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The burden of the cross chastises the proud!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.30,0:20:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cross is the way of repentance!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.07,0:20:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Sister Agnese such a great prize for all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.90,0:20:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no longer any safe harbor for that woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.59,0:20:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you understand that, you pagan monkey?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.17,0:20:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who needs to understand that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.10,0:20:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who'd accept that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.70,0:20:53.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cross is the way of repentance!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.10,0:20:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Biagio!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.85,0:20:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His left hand?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.09,0:21:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used my own attack?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I'll fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.71,0:21:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you dare lay a finger on Agnese again,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.90,0:21:19.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll beat you down to a pulp.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.32,0:21:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Touma!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.36,0:21:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you come to?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.85,0:21:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Adriatic Sea isn't all that cold, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.24,0:22:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you look so happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.65,0:22:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it because I didn't abandon you this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.65,0:22:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's not like I'm happy or anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.34,0:22:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a phone call, Touma.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.25,0:22:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come back to Academy City right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.91,0:22:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be troublesome for other\Nfacilities to be poking around your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.66,0:22:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There should be a supersonic jet sitting\Naround in the Academy City airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.31,0:22:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I haven't even been in Italy for a whole day—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.80,0:22:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.86,0:22:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some girl came looking for you earlier and left a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.54,0:22:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"When you get back, be prepared for\Nthe penalty game from the Daihaseisai."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.65,0:22:44.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Misaka Mikoto?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.42,0:22:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wai— Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.02,0:22:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.56,0:22:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.09,0:22:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.50,0:22:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you should really ask the Amakusa people\Nrather than me if you want a debriefing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.29,0:22:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm no longer associated with the Amakusa Church...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.93,0:23:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True as that is, you sure dragged Kami-yan\Ninto a lot of trouble again, Nee-chin.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.59,0:23:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, even serving him as his personal maid\Nfor a whole day wouldn't be enough to cover it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.44,0:23:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hey, why don't I lend you the fallen\Nangel maid battle costume I have?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.52,0:23:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can use that as your battle outfit!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.67,0:23:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of ridiculous crap are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.85,0:23:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And why do you have something like that anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.63,0:23:27.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're one of only 20 Saints in the\Nworld. I'm sure you're prepared for—
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.47,0:23:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Like this, Touma...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.49,0:23:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.57,0:24:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I accidentally picked up more luggage on the way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.29,0:24:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that was a bit rushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.72,0:24:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think you're talking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.73,0:24:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand who it is {\i1}you're{\i0} running your mouth off at?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.78,0:24:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Pope.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.61,0:24:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.52,0:24:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you treat me badly, you're going to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.65,0:24:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Right Seat of God...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.73,0:24:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The title of Pope means nothing to you, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.94,0:24:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Read this and sign it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.88,0:24:39.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're giving {\i1}me{\i0} an order?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.14,0:24:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, this document is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.62,0:24:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were planning on issuing the order yourself at some point, no?
